  "prompt": "When being sworn in as a witness in a court of law, and you are asked if you swear to tell the truth what happens if you say no?",
  "response": "If you are asked to swear or affirm to tell the truth in a court of law and you respond with \"no,\" you generally cannot proceed as a witness. The court requires witnesses to take an oath or affirmation to ensure that their testimony is given under the seriousness of legal obligation to be truthful. If a person refuses to take the oath or affirmation, they may not be allowed to testify at all. Additionally, refusing to testify or comply with the oath could lead to legal consequences, including being held in contempt of court.",
